    public interface FitnessFunction

    • Method Detail

      • fitness

        int fitness(java.lang.String individual)
        Returns the fitness of individual. The result is a non-negative number. Higher numbers indicate more fit individuals.

      • isOptimal

        boolean isOptimal(java.lang.String individual)
        Returns true if individual has the highest possible fitness. This is for efficient early stopping; algorithms will still work (albeit more slowly) if this method always returns false.
